1. js library to build UI.
2. Component Based Architecture (not webpages).
3. Used to create single page application(SPA) (only one HTML page).
4. very fast because of virtual DOM.
5. lifecycle method - render() - compulsory -(code that defines appearance of components).
6. All react components should have single responsibility principle.

1. Browser does not understand the language in react js thats why we do transpilation using vanilla JS.
2. In react JS there is hierarchial tree relationship that means no component is isolated.
3. React is a front end JavaScript library developed by Facebook in 2011. 
4. It follows the component based approach which helps in building reusable UI components. 
5. It is used for developing complex and interactive web and mobile UI.
6. It uses the virtual DOM instead of the real DOM.
7. It uses server-side rendering.
8. It follows uni-directional data flow or data binding.